body:
My bullish case: AMC keeps doing press releases where they insist that A-list grew much higher and faster than what they expected. This implies that they beat vs. what they had announced, and they raise guidance vs, what they had announced. 

&amp;#x200B;

My bearish case: how much money does AMC lose because of A-list? If someone used to go 5 times to the movies and now can go those 5 times or even more but for cheaper thanks to A-list, AMC would be losing money. 

&amp;#x200B;

What are your thoughts?
